        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-12 10:53:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe jira issue describes the Nexus IQ findings.  I believe upgrading to 2.8.10 will solve this CVE:\n\nCVE-2017-7525\n\nA deserialization flaw was discovered in the jackson-databind, versions before 2.6.7.1, 2.7.9.1 and 2.8.9, which could allow an unauthenticated user to perform code execution by sending the maliciously crafted input to the readValue method of the ObjectMapper.\nExplanation",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "97a98c1ce6a63d643d40a64c7b5b4755000fd0c9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1423,
          "name": "Rob Daugherty",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "rd472p@att.com",
          "username": "rd472p"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-12 10:57:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBut you are right, there is still a CVE on version 2.8.10, which we cannot solve without also upgrading springboot.  I still think we should upgrade to 2.8.10 which will reduce the count of critical vulnerabilities by one.\n\nSonatype CWE: 502\nVersion: 2.8.11.1\n\njackson-databind is vulnerable to Remote Code Execution (RCE). The createBeanDeserializer() function in the BeanDeserializerFactory class allows untrusted Java objects to be deserialized. A remote attacker can exploit this by uploading a malicious serialized object that will result in RCE if the application attempts to deserialize it.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
